# .secrets-allowlist
#
# Each non-blank, non-comment line is an ERE regex applied to the entire line
# of source code that triggered the secret scanner.  If any pattern here
# matches, the hit is silently suppressed.
#
# IMPORTANT: Keep entries specific.  Broad catch-all words like "test" or
# "sample" can inadvertently suppress real secrets.  Prefer anchored literals
# or very narrow patterns.
#
# Alternatively, append  # secrets-ignore  to a single source line to silence
# that line only without changing this file.
#
# ── Safe placeholder / documentation values ───────────────────────────────────

# Obvious placeholder text that is never a real credential
(YOUR_API_KEY|YOUR_SECRET_KEY|YOUR_SECRET|REPLACE_ME|INSERT_KEY_HERE|<API_KEY>|<SECRET>)

# Environment-variable look-ups (the value comes from the environment, not hardcoded)
process\.env\.|import\.meta\.env\.
